{
  "text": "In a report of PEG as an outpatient procedure in HNC patients, Mello et al. used cervical fistula and pharyngoesophagostomies as the access route for introducing the endoscope and the PEG tube in 6 (4.6 %) of a total of 136 patients [CITATION_1] .",
